      • getPreviousEntry

        public IVirtualDiskEntry getPreviousEntry()
        Returns the previous virtual disk entry. Every virtual disk entry (except the root directory) is part of a doubly linked list containing virtual disk entries (IVirtualDiskEntry) that are on the same hierarchical level, therefore they have the same parent (IVirtualDiskEntry.getParent()). This method will return the previous entry in this doubly linked list. It returns null if there is no previous member.
        Specified by:
        getPreviousEntry in interface IVirtualDiskEntry
        Returns:
        previous member or null if there is none
        See Also:
        IVirtualDirectory.getFirstMember()
